summary: A customer is frustrated that they have not received a delivery of 10kg of goods which they ordered from Mitramart Supermarket last week. The caller is transferred to the complaint department where they are asked for their details and the details of their order which they provide. It is suggested that the order may have been placed with a distributor called Varath Gopal and the caller is put on hold while the complaint department contact the distributor. It is hoped that the issue can be resolved within the next few days.
speaker_a_summary: The caller is trying to file a complaint and needs to provide their name, phone number, address and the name of the salesman and distributor who sold them the product for the complaint to go forward. The caller can also provide an alternative method of contact such as an email if they have it. The problem has been ongoing for an unspecified amount of time and the product involved is causing problems. The call will be put on hold while the complaint is registered and the caller should continue on the line and not disconnect.
speaker_b_summary: Nick needs to make some money so he can pay off his debt to a local gangster named Kesar. He calls various shops in the hope of getting them to supply him with liquor to sell on to his friends but none are able to help him. He also tries to get a job at a local supermarket but is told they are not hiring.

- The company is not willing to provide the product and is not offering any alternatives. 
- The customer is asking for the name and number of a manager so they can make a complaint. 
- The customer is also asking for the details of the call to be noted down.
